TITLE: Defining a Basic tRPC Router in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to define a simple tRPC router with a greeting procedure. This creates an API endpoint that can be exposed to the frontend through an adapter.
SOURCE: https://github.com/trpc/trpc/blob/main/www/docs/server/routers.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import * as trpc from '@trpc/server';
// ---cut---
import { publicProcedure, router } from './trpc';

const appRouter = router({
  greeting: publicProcedure.query(() => 'hello tRPC v10!'),
});

// Export only the type of a router!
// This prevents us from importing server code on the client.
export type AppRouter = typeof appRouter;
```

