TITLE: Setting up tRPC Client in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to set up a tRPC client using the httpBatchLink. It imports the AppRouter type from the server to ensure type safety.
SOURCE: https://github.com/trpc/trpc/blob/main/www/docs/main/quickstart.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { createTRPCClient, httpBatchLink } from '@trpc/client';
import type { AppRouter } from './server';
//     ðŸ‘† **type-only** import

// Pass AppRouter as generic here. ðŸ‘‡ This lets the `trpc` object know
// what procedures are available on the server and their input/output types.
const trpc = createTRPCClient<AppRouter>({
  links: [
    httpBatchLink({
      url: 'http://localhost:3000',
    }),
  ],
});
```

