TITLE: Defining tRPC Server Router in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create a tRPC router with procedures for listing, retrieving, and creating posts. It uses Zod for input validation and defines the AppRouter type.
SOURCE: https://github.com/trpc/trpc/blob/main/www/versioned_docs/version-10.x/client/react/infer-types.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { initTRPC } from '@trpc/server';
import { z } from "zod";

const t = initTRPC.create();

const appRouter = t.router({
  post: t.router({
    list: t.procedure
      .query(() => {
        // imaginary db call
        return [{ id: 1, title: 'tRPC is the best!' }];
    }),
    byId: t.procedure
      .input(z.string())
      .query(({ input }) => {
        // imaginary db call
        return { id: 1, title: 'tRPC is the best!' };
    }),
    create: t.procedure
      .input(z.object({ title: z.string(), text: z.string(), }))
      .mutation(({ input }) => {
        // imaginary db call
        return { id: 1, ...input };
    }),
  }),
});

export type AppRouter = typeof appRouter;
```

