TITLE: Logging Procedure Execution Time with tRPC Middleware in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript example shows how to add a logging middleware to a tRPC router. It records the start time, executes the next middleware or procedure using `await next()`, calculates the duration, and logs details like path, type, and duration using a mock logging function (`logMock`). The middleware applies to all subsequent procedures ('foo', 'abc') in the router chain.
SOURCE: https://github.com/trpc/trpc/blob/main/www/versioned_docs/version-9.x/server/middlewares.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: ts
CODE:
```
trpc
  .router<Context>()
  .middleware(async ({ path, type, next }) => {
    const start = Date.now();
    const result = await next();
    const durationMs = Date.now() - start;
    result.ok
      ? logMock('OK request timing:', { path, type, durationMs })
      : logMock('Non-OK request timing', { path, type, durationMs });

    return result;
  })
  .query('foo', {
    resolve() {
      return 'bar';
    },
  })
  .query('abc', {
    resolve() {
      return 'def';
    },
  });
```

