TITLE: Extending Middlewares with unstable_pipe() in tRPC
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to extend middlewares using the unstable_pipe() method. It shows how to create and pipe middlewares together, and how the order of piping affects the resulting context.
SOURCE: https://github.com/trpc/trpc/blob/main/www/docs/server/middlewares.md#2025-04-23_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const fooMiddleware = t.middleware((opts) => {
  return opts.next({
    ctx: {
      foo: 'foo' as const,
    },
  });
});

const barMiddleware = fooMiddleware.unstable_pipe((opts) => {
  const { ctx } = opts;
  ctx.foo;
  //   ^?
  return opts.next({
    ctx: {
      bar: 'bar' as const,
    },
  });
});

const barProcedure = publicProcedure.use(barMiddleware);
barProcedure.query(({ ctx }) => ctx.bar);
//                              ^?
```

