TITLE: Customizing tRPC Error Formatting in Server (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: Defines a tRPC router and uses the `formatError` method to modify the default error shape. It checks if the error code is 'BAD_REQUEST' and the cause is a ZodError, adding the flattened ZodError details to the 'data.zodError' field. This allows structured validation errors to be passed to the client.
SOURCE: https://github.com/trpc/trpc/blob/main/www/versioned_docs/version-9.x/server/error-formatting.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

