TITLE: Implementing tRPC Router with Hello Procedure in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This backend code snippet demonstrates how to create a tRPC router with a 'hello' procedure. It uses Zod for input validation and defines a query that returns a greeting.
SOURCE: https://github.com/trpc/trpc/blob/main/www/versioned_docs/version-10.x/client/react/useQuery.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import { initTRPC } from '@trpc/server';
import { z } from 'zod';

export const t = initTRPC.create();

export const appRouter = t.router({
  // Create procedure at path 'hello'
  hello: t.procedure
    // using zod schema to validate and infer input values
    .input(
      z
        .object({
          text: z.string().nullish(),
        })
        .nullish(),
    )
    .query((opts) => {
      return {
        greeting: `hello ${opts.input?.text ?? 'world'}`,
      };
    }),
});
```

