TITLE: Defining a Basic tRPC Server with Router and Procedures
DESCRIPTION: Sets up a tRPC server with a router containing procedures for listing posts, getting posts by ID, and creating posts. This is the foundation for the type inference examples that follow.
SOURCE: https://github.com/trpc/trpc/blob/main/www/docs/client/react/infer-types.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// @module: esnext
// @filename: server.ts
import { initTRPC } from '@trpc/server';
import { z } from "zod";

const t = initTRPC.create();

const appRouter = t.router({
  post: t.router({
    list: t.procedure
      .query(() => {
        // imaginary db call
        return [{ id: 1, title: 'tRPC is the best!' }];
    }),
    byId: t.procedure
      .input(z.string())
      .query(({ input }) => {
        // imaginary db call
        return { id: 1, title: 'tRPC is the best!' };
    }),
    create: t.procedure
      .input(z.object({ title: z.string(), text: z.string(), }))
      .mutation(({ input }) => {
        // imaginary db call
        return { id: 1, ...input };
    }),
  }),
});

export type AppRouter = typeof appRouter;
```

